description: {"blocks":[{"key":"9q1pq","text":"This protocol describes the passaging of trophoblast organoids isolated from full-term human placental tissue. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

groups.title: Protocol for isolation and passaging of trophoblast organoids from full-term placental tissue--Coyne lab, Duke University

manuscript_citation: Innate immune signaling in trophoblast and decidua organoids defines differential antiviral defenses at the maternal-fetal interface Liheng Yang, Eleanor C. Semmes, Cristian Ovies, Christina Megli, Sallie Permar, Jennifer B. Gilner, Carolyn B. Coyne

status.info: We have successfully used this protocol for over two years for the passaging of trophoblast organoids isolated from full-term placental tissue.

steps.section: Reagents, Solutions and Materials prepared in advance:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2e0oe","text":"a) Pre-cool blunt 200 µl pipette tips (Fisher 02-707-134).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":3,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1vnc6","text":"b) Pre-warm multi-well TC plate (this protocol uses 24-well TC plate, cat# 3526, Costar) and Stem Pro Accutase (Gibco, Cat # A11105-01) supplemented with 10 µM Y-27632 (Sigma, Y0503-1MG; 100 × dilution from stock solution, this is Rock inhibitor used to prevent the stem cells from anoikis during the passaging process).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":3,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dkhau","text":"c) Pre-thaw Matrigel (Corning 356231)on the ice for at least 2 hrs, we usually thaw it o/n on the ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":3,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ie5q","text":"d) Prepare 20% (vol/vol) FBS medium and basal media as needed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":3,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3d9l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1tecr","text":"Remove complete growth medium (TOM) from each well. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"76cuu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7iasa","text":"Add 500 ul of fresh basal medium(Advanced DMEM/F12, Life Technologies, 12634-010) to each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"74lc5","text":"Pre-coat a wide orifice 1 ml pipette tip (Finntip 1000, Thermo Fisher, 9405160) using FBS-containing basal media media and use this tip to gently scrape off the Matrigel domes (including organoids) without touching the bottom of the well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5a5ej","text":"Using the same wide orifice tip, carefully transfer the released mixture of Matrigel and organoids into a 15 ml conical centrifuge tube and briefly pipette several times.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ajv86","text":"Centrifuge a t600 RPM, RT for 6 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5vc6a","text":"Carefully remove supernatant as much as possible using a 1 ml pipette and then remove remaining media using a 200uL tip if necessary; do not use glass Pasteur pipette or vacuum to aspirate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"jrem","text":"Add 1 ml of pre-warmed dissociation reagent:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1omni","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5si7t","text":"a. StemPro Accutase (Life Technologies, A11105-01) or TrypLE express Life Technologies, 12605-028). Pre-warm prior to use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4ievm","text":"b. Add ROCK inhibitor to dissociation agent; for 1 ml of dissociation agent, add 10 ul of inhibitor.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"67t7h","text":"Incubate in 37℃ water bath for 6-10 min and swirl from time to time during this incubation. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3oq72","text":"Centrifuge at 600 RPM, RT for 6 min. Repeat step for an additional 6min if organoids have not pelleted. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6vnk2","text":"Remove supernatant as much as possible by using 1 ml pipette and then remove remaining media using a 200uL tip if necessary; do not use glass Pasteur pipette to aspirate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bgfcb","text":"Add 200 ul of basal medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9acbc","text":"Use autopipette (Eppendorf Xplorer plus, 1-channel, variable, 15 – 300 µL,  4861000031) to disturb/resuspend pellet (pipetting times depend on organoid size).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"jl75","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f766h","text":"a. Set autopipette to full force (level 8)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"48c9g","text":"b. Pipette 200x","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d41hg","text":"c. Check suspension","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5bpas","text":"d. Pipette 50x","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fujhl","text":"e. Check suspension","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"408fd","text":"f. Pipette 30x if not evenly disrupted","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ei802","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8jrue","text":"Remove but do not discard autopipette tip.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b2sr","text":"Flush inside of autopipette tip using 1 ml of basal medium into above solution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fmlsb","text":"Centrifuge at 600 RPM, RT for 6 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1o9g2","text":"Remove supernatant using 1 ml pipette; do not use glass Pasteur pipette to aspirate, then put the 15 ml conical tube with pellet into ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b522e","text":"Resuspend the pellet with pre-thawed Matrigel using pre-cooled blunt 200 µl pipette tips (Fisher 02-707-134), the amount of Matrigel: 40 X number of wells desired.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"birv5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c46fg","text":"a.For example, for 6 wells, add 240-250 ul of Matrigel.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"487i0","text":"b.Matrigel should be kept on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"83dan","text":"c.Do not discard pipette tip; transfer to 20-200ul pipette.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"60ab9","text":"Carefully dispense 40 ul aliquot of Matrigel-organoid suspension into pre-warm 24-well plate using cold pipette tip to create a \"dome\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3rpao","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"be6aj","text":"a. Do not touch the bottom of the plate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aeqp4","text":"b. Slowly and carefully lift up pipette tip as dispensing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fnp8b","text":"c. Do not push pipette tip fully down as this will introduce bubbles.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7d8l3","text":"Place 24-well plate in 37℃incubator for 2 minutes to allow Matrigel to pre-polymerize.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8rm34","text":"Flip the plate and incubate additional 8 minutes to fully polymerize and evenly distribute the organoid fragments throughout the  Matrigel.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"109di","text":"During the polymerization process, prepare TOM with Y-27632 with 200 × dilution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fi6ht","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5vcrp","text":"a.Need 500 ul of medium/well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"765j6","text":"b.For example, for 6 wells, need 3 ml of medium with 15 ul of ROCK inhibitor.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3gnj0","text":"Submerge the polymerized Matrigel domes with 500 µl TOM per well, and culture them in 37℃ humidified CO2 incubator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":103,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"81v3n","text":"Observe daily and renew the TOM every 48-72 hrs. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":48,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f5trc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"cost","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"546D70401E6211ED9A8807818E4CAA57","id":0,"value":""}}}}
